<hl>
<seg id=1> China Has Approved the Establishment of More Than 300,000 Enterprises With Foreign Investment  </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, December 25, Telegram (Reporter Lu Yongjian).  The latest news from the Ministry of Foreign Economics and Trade is that as of the end of November of this year, China has approved the establishment of a total of 302,464 enterprises with foreign investment. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> According to the information provided, these more than 300,000 enterprises with foreign investment consist of 182,059 Chinese-foreign joint ventures, accounting for 60 percent; 44,094 Chinese-foreign cooperative business enterprises, accounting for about 15 percent; and 76,161 foreign firm sole proprietorships, accounting for about 25 percent. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Currently, the pattern of China employing diverse foreign firm investment has begun to emerge; the sources of capital lie in more than 170 countries and regions. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> As of the end of September of this year, arranged in order by amount of foreign capital actually employed, the top ten countries and regions that have invested the most in China are:  Hong Kong, Taiwan, Japan, the U.S., Singapore, Korea, Great Britain, Germany, the Virgin Islands, and France. </seg>
<seg id=6> In investment in China, these top ten countries and regions account for more than 91 percent of the amount of foreign capital actually employed throughout China. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> Asian countries and regions are the main source of foreign capital for China.  The amount of investment from Hong Kong, Taiwan, Japan, Korea, the ASEAN countries, and other countries and regions accounts for more than 85 percent of the total amount of foreign investment actually used throughout China. </seg>
<seg id=8> Of these, Hong Kong is still the main source of foreign capital absorbed by inland areas, accounting for more than 55 percent of the total foreign investment absorbed. </seg>
</p>
